        <a title="Cathy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cathy" href="/user/show/978552-cathy">Cathy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" 9780747553977" href="/book/show/2484972.Apricots_on_the_Nile">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17379203" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5290593975826662031">A cute little book with nice recipes of the typical Egyptian food you still get today and some others with a French twist. The book is more a collection of little anecdotes than a fully flung story. Fairly shallow and superficial, but still worth reading for the feel-good factor. If you like food, this is a good choice. You can see and smell those kitchens in vivid detail.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


